    "body": "@SeeminglyScience **Bzzt! Wrong answer.** The last item is correct, i.e., you need four backticks (`` ` ``). Try this script to see for yourself.\r\n\r\n```PowerShell\r\nOut-File -LiteralPath '[By serial number] TMZ-A01.lib'\r\n# â†‘ Creates \"[By serial number] TMZ-A01.lib\"\r\n\r\nOut-File -Path \"`[By serial number`] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib\" -InputObject \"Test\"\r\n# â†‘ Out-File: Cannot perform operation because the wildcard path\r\n# [By serial number] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib did not resolve to a file.\r\n\r\nOut-File -Path \"``[By serial number``] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib\" -InputObject \"Test\"\r\n# â†‘ Out-File: Cannot perform operation because the wildcard path\r\n# `[By serial number`] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib did not resolve to a file.\r\n\r\nOut-File -Path \"```[By serial number```] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib\" -InputObject \"Test\"\r\n# â†‘ Out-File: Cannot perform operation because the wildcard path\r\n# `[By serial number`] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib did not resolve to a file.\r\n\r\nOut-File -Path \"````[By serial number````] TMZ-[ABCDEF]01.lib\" -InputObject \"Test\"\r\n# â†‘ SUCCESS!\r\n```\r\n\r\n@iSazonov Given the above, can you at least see my concern?",
